      m_Calls: []
  m_text: 'Botanical Name:

    Boerhavia diffusa L


    Common Names: Spreading
    Hogweed, Red Spiderling, Horse Purslane.


    Habitat: Tropical & Subtropical
    Regions, whrive h, roadsides, waste ground.


    Medicinal Uses:

    Diuretic,
    Anti-Inflammatiory, Hepatprotecive.

    Used for kidney & liver support, joint
    pain, anemia,Traditional Ayurvedic medicine.


    Cultivation

    Propagation:
    Seeds or Stem Cuttings.

    Soil: Well-drained, Average Fertillity.

    Sunlight:
    Full sun or Partcial shade Watering

    Moderate. Drought-Tolerant once established'
